
[1]elegantly

   EL'EGANTLY, adv. In a manner to please; with elegance; with beauty;
   with pleasing propriety; as a composition elegantly written.

   1. With due symmetry; with well formed and duly proportioned parts; as
   a house elegantly built.

   2. Richly; with rich or handsome materials well disposed; as a room
   elegantly furnished; a woman elegantly dressed.
